<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/fuel-pump-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&#038;ssl=1" alt="Breaking: Buhari approves reduction of Petroleum pump price to N130" align="left" style="margin: 0 20px 20px 0;max-width:100%" data-recalc-dims="1" /> President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the reduction in pump price of premium motor spirit (PMS) from N145 per liter to about N130. Presidency sources hinted that the approval followed presentation by minister of state petroleum resources Mr Timipre Sylva to the Federal Executive Council (FEC), on Wednesday. The sources claimed that the Minister briefed the council on the need to reduce the pump price following the global fall in oil price. It was reliably gathered that outbreak of COVID-19, has made the international crude oil price to crash  from $60 to $30, causing fear of a possible economic crisis. The sources that going forward, the government would allow the international price of crude to determine the prices of the product in Nigeria. Meanwhile, the Minister of State, Petroleum Resources according to uncomfirmed information has scheduled to meet with members of the organized Labour in the oil and gas sector before proceeding to make the formal announcement for the  price adjustment. Details later: Vanguard The post Breaking: Buhari approves reduction of Petroleum pump price to N130 appeared first on Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard First name * Email * Phone Number  Check your inbox or spam folder to confirm your subscription. …C’ttee to assess impact of Coronavirus on 2020 budget By Johnbosco Agbakwuru PRESIDENT Muhammadu Buhari yesterday set up a committee to assess the impact of the ravaging coronavirus on the economy, especially the 2020.budget. The committee is saddled with the responsibility of revisiting the crude oil benchmark price of $53… March 10, 2020 In "News" The Inter-ministerial committee inaugurated on Monday by President Muhammadu Buhari 